     <div type="to_the_reader">
   <pb n="321" facs="164"/>
   <head>To The Reader.</head>
   <p>
      <seg rend="decorInit">I</seg>F you are satisfied with my <hi>Emblems,</hi> I here set before you a second service. It is an Aegyptian dish, drest on the English fashion: They, at their Feasts, used to present a Deaths-head at their second course; This will serve for both: You need not feare a surfet: Here is but little; And that, light of digestion: If it but please your Palate, I question not your stomack: Fall too; and much good may't doe you.</p>
   <closer>
      <signed>
         <hi>Covivio addit Minerval.</hi> E. B.</signed>
   </closer>
   <epigraph>
      <q>Rem, Regem, Regimen, Regionem, Relligionem, Exornat, celebrat, laudat, honorat, amat.</q>
   </epigraph>
   <closer>
      <salute>BENEVOLUS.</salute>
   </closer>
</div>
